      <h2 style="padding-top: 6px">About this app</h2>
      <p>
        This app provides various examples that show how to build dashboards, forms, and views for Splunk 5+. The app contains two sections:
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          <b><a href="/app/dashboard_examples/dashboard1">Simple XML Dashboards and Forms</a></b>
          <br />Splunk recommends that you start with simple XML. Most of the basic functionality for dashboards and forms is available with simple XML.
        </p>
        <p>
          You do not need to be a professional coder to use Splunk's simple XML.
          Splunk provides interactive editors to get you started with dashboards.
          You can then enhance the generated dashboards with a few tweaks to the simple XML code.
          Splunk provides an embedded XML Editor to help you update the XML code.
        </p>
        <p>
          <b><a href="/app/dashboard_examples/advanced_intro1">Advanced XML</a></b>
          <br />Use advanced XML to create custom dashboards with advanced features.
          Advanced XML, as the name implies, is for advanced users with significant programming experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you want to learn more about a particular module refer to the
          <a target="_blank" href="http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/5.0/AdvancedDev/ModuleReference">Module Reference</a> available from Splunk core documentation. 
          You can also access the <a href="../../modules">generated module reference</a> that is available from your own Splunk instance. 
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      
